<p>The <b>Happy Station Show</b> is the world's longest-running international radio programme, having originated in 1928 on <a href="/wiki/Shortwave_radio" title="Shortwave radio">shortwave radio</a>. Its run has been interrupted twice - from 1940 until 1946 due to World War II and again from 1995 when it was cancelled until its revival in 2009.<sup id="cite_ref-DXing_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-DXing-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
